{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17512197","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17512197"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:51:48+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:51:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11858"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11858","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11858"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.03,0.73,0.1,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4458"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43688"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4458","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4458"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11858"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28689"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"1"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"26"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"646"},{"type":"tags","id":"2551"},{"type":"tags","id":"2706"},{"type":"tags","id":"4897"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"5595"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11627"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"6439"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6443"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42673"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44700"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43688","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/43688"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 61-year-old man is undergoing an emergency laparotomy. He has an increased body habitus with a BMI of 37 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E. After a rapid-sequence induction, a right subclavian central venous catheter is inserted following two failed attempts of insertion into the right internal jugular vein. Approximately 30 minutes into the procedure, the anaesthetist notices an increase in airway pressure, rise in heart rate to 120/min and a decrease in SpO2 to 88 %.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely cause of the patient\u0027s deterioration?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Endobronchial intubation","Anaphylaxis","Tension pneumothorax","Severe bronchospasm","Kinking of the endotracheal tube"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPneumothorax\u003C/strong\u003E is one of the complications which can follow insertion of a subclavian central venous cannulation (CVC). Provided that the cannula goes directly from its skin insertion under the clavicle into the subclavian vein, there should be no problems. However, if the catheter tip is misdirected and the vein missed, the pleura can easily be damaged. That is most likely what has happened in this case and with the patient being ventilated, air has been forced through the pleural tear into the pleural space, causing a pneumothorax.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESevere bronchospasm\u003C/strong\u003E is an alternative diagnosis. The clinical history, however, with a difficult central line insertion, is suggestive of a tension pneumothorax.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFurther complications of CVC insertion can be grouped according to the following:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EImmediate: bleeding, arterial puncture, air embolism, malposition, pneumothorax, haemothorax\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDelayed: infection, venous thrombosis, venous stenosis, catheter migration, catheter embolism, myocardial perforation, nerve injury\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnaphylaxis\u003C/strong\u003E may present with similar clinical features of tachycardia, hypotension and increased airway pressure, but is most likely to occur at induction or following a particular drug administration.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWithout any movement of the head, a \u003Cstrong\u003Ekinking of the endotracheal tube\u003C/strong\u003E would be most unusual. There is nothing in the stem to suggest that there has been any movement.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Pneumothorax can be a potentially devastating complication of central venous catheter insertion"],"references":["Overview of complications of central venous catheters and their prevention in adults. In: Uptodate [online]. 2023. Available at: https://www.uptodate.com/contents/overview-of-complications-of-central-venous-catheters-and-their-prevention-in-adults?search=central%20venous%20catheters\u0026source=search_result\u0026selectedTitle=3~150\u0026usage_type=default\u0026display_rank=3#H17","Tran J, Hausssner W, Shah K. Traumatic Pneumothorax: A Review of Current Diagnostic Practices And Evolving Management. J Emerg Med 2021; 61:517\u201328"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28689"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11858"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28689","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/28689"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-03-25T15:32:42+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-03-25T15:32:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4458"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43688"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"1","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude34","name":"Anaesthesia","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"created